    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-28T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-28T05:00:00-05:00" n="903"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d903">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">361.1121 Roszkowski, Mieczyslaw/14:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-28T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >February 28, 1941—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 28—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>388. My 275, February 13, 3 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>] p.m.<note n="32"
                        xml:id="d903fn32">Not printed.</note> The Embassy is in receipt of a note
                    from the Commissariat for Foreign Affairs to the effect that the “Mechislav
                    Ignatevich Rozhkovski, who was born in 1920, has been sentenced by the public
                    court of Lapski <hi rend="italic">raion</hi> to 3 years of reformatory labor
                    camp for unlawful keeping of arms.[”] The note further states that Rozhkovski
                    “has a birth certificate attested to by the city clerk at the city of Fall
                    River, Massachusetts, United States of America” but no other documents to
                    confirm his American citizenship.</p>
                <p>I am addressing a further note to the Commissariat for Foreign Affairs
                    reasserting Rozhkovski’s American citizenship and requesting permission for a
                    representative of the Embassy to interview him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
